features: The Ultimate Oral Care Setup – HDCPro is all you need for perfect oral hygiene. It features a state-of-the-art power toothbrush packed with all our advanced technology, a compact water flosser with multiple pressure settings and modes – all in one sleek, neat and compact setup. Brush and seamlessly switch to flossing with our oral irrigator that reduces flossing time by 90% while dramatically improving gum health.

Flossing Made Easy – No more excuses on why you didn’t have time to floss. HDCPro drastically simplifies flossing by using a more modern method which replaces traditional string floss with gentle targeted water pressure. Our water flosser features a hygienic 600ml tank with a 10-level adjustable water pressure dial. It also includes deep clean and soothing massage modes to reinvigorate your gums and smile. Flossing now takes seconds instead of minutes, and without the string mess.

A Modern Power Toothbrush – HDCPro also brings toothbrushes into modern times, featuring our Black Series Pro power toothbrush with its built-in enhanced features. An advanced 50,000 Vibrations Per Minute motor, a lithium-ion battery, ultra-fast wireless charging (forget outdated USB charging), 5 distinct brushing modes and a smart vibrating notification timer are some of the enhanced features built into the sleek and ergonomic waterproof black satin handle.

Sleek, Neat & Compact – HDCPro measures just 6 inches across and 3 inches wide saving you precious countertop space. Premium materials include ultra-hygienic satin rubber and anodized metallic finishes to ensure a sleek addition to any bathroom space.

What’s in the Box – 1 Home Dental Center Pro Countertop Setup, 1 Black Series Pro Electric Toothbrush, 6 ProFlex Brush heads, 2 water flosser jet tips, 1 tongue scraper, 1 power adapter, warranty card, and user manual.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Home Dental Center Pro is the ultimate 2-in-1 oral care setup. Save precious counter space while getting your cleanest and most confident smile.

It boasts a 40,000 Vibrations Per Minute motor, 2-minute auto shut-off timer, 30-second vibration indicator, and 4 cleaning modes:Clean, Soft, Whiten, and Massage. The waterproof handle is powered by a lithium-ion battery, which charges wirelessly in a matter of just a couple hours. ...and FlossingMade Easy on the Other Side The aqua flosser drastically simplifies flossing by using a more modern method which replaces traditional string floss with gentle yet powerful targeted water pressure. Our water flosser features a large, 20 oz. tank with a 10-level adjustable water pressure dial. It also includes deep clean and soothing massage modes to reinvigorate your gums. Reduce your flossing time by 90%while improving your oral health. . . and without the string mess.

6 Brush Heads Included Forget spending more money on extra attachments. It also comes with a tongue scraper tip, for a whole mouth clean. Superior Clean Made Easy The toothbrush’s powerful motor and 2-minute timer make it easy to achieve your best brushing ever. Aqua Flosser provides complete flossing in 20 seconds with no strings attached. Literally.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is awesome !!
reviews.reviewText: My dental hygienist recommended me to go with a rechargeable toothbrush and water pick combo due to some gum issues developing. I had always used a battery-operated toothbrush, and thought I was doing a pretty good job of cleaning my teeth. Wow, this kit does an amazing job, and it is also affordable.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars What is most important to you?
reviews.reviewText: Very light. Small enough to travel with. Easy to clean. Water pressure on the flosser is perfect and it comes with different heads to change out.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Vibrates, doesn’t brush
reviews.reviewText: Everything about this product feels great. Feels solid in the hand. Has kind of an anti-skid rubber that allows the toothbrush to be held when wet. There’s just some minor annoyances I can’t get over. It apparently has a built-in timer I didn’t read anything about in the description. Every 30-seconds it shuts off for several seconds, which is supposed to indicate it’s time to move to another quadrant. Then at 2 minutes it shuts off completely. Super annoying.And then the brush head just vibrates. Don’t get me wrong, my teeth feel really clean after, and I can’t say it does a bad job. But I can’t get the idea that an actual moving brush head would be better.I haven’t used the water pick or tongue scraper so I can’t verify any of that, but I did mess with the dial and it turned on and blew air at me. Seems like something I would probably enjoy.Overall, it seems to be really good quality and I can’t fault it for what it is.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars The water flosser built poorly and is messy
reviews.reviewText: So the first thing I actually thought this was a Philips sonic and this is how the company fools you because they put aqua sonic in the name. Am I impressed with a brush? Heck yeah it’s actually just as good as a Philips sonic it’s got four settings and I usually leave mine on whitening. I’ll probably try the other three later on down the road but for now all I care is about wine in my teeth. Now the downfall of this particular product is the water fossler, it is built poorly because of the extended cable that isn’t flexible and when you turn it to clean the water jets all over the place as you can see on one of the photos I have provided. It also didn’t work properly the first time around and for whatever reason it’s working correctly now but I have noticed that I have to fill the tank almost every day now that it’s working properly because of the amount of water it shoots out I even turned the knob down so that shoots out slower but it’s still messy. This is the most messy water fossler I’ve ever had.I would’ve given this five stars but that is the only downfall this particular product. I do like how they provide more brush heads and fossler options Than Philip sonic does and it’s a good bargain for the price I ended up paying $70 it was on sale and I like the brush that it’s black it looks way better than that traditional white brush.

reviews.reviewTitle: Nice combo that works well and costs less, but has some weak spots compared to brand leaders
reviews.reviewText: My previous water flosser, the brand leader, developed a leaky line. I also wanted to get an electric toothbrush, having previously owned a brand leader that died long ago. As I was looking into brand leaders for both, and for combo units, I came across AquaSonic. What stood out for me was the cost of toothbrushes. That's where the brand leaders really get you. So not only did the AquaSonic cost less on the initial purchase, I expect its lifetime cost of ownership to be less. The flosser works well, and is MUCH quieter than my previous flosser. It's also more powerful, which took some getting used to. I use it now on the lowest or second lowest setting. Maybe I'll be able to increase that over time. The toothbrush works quite well. I was used to the round brush with circular cleaning motion of the brand leader, so the sonic action of this model was new for me. But after a couple of days I got used to it. One thing that I found a bit annoying is that the buttons are easy to accidentally press while you are brushing, thus turning it off or changing the brushing mode. Recessed buttons or some contour of the handle would have prevented this. I've adapted to it by holding the brush at the very bottom so my hands aren't near the buttons. Comes with five identical brushes, two waterpicks (why not five?), and a tongue cleaner. But, there's no colour coding. I'm not sharing this unit with anyone so it's not an issue for me. But for a couple it's a bit inconvenient, especially since popping the toothbrush off takes a bit of effort -- unlike the flosser which has an eject button. I also worry about the durability of the water line for the flosser. There's no strain relieve on it so I suspect it will crack and leak after a few years of use, same as my old brand-leader flosser.
This works amazingly. I feel like I just left the dentist office. I've never used a water pick and it has changed my life.
Size is good is not to bigQuality is goodIt’s not to noisyAnd have some extra stuff on it
